# PGSD kernel configuration
#
# Minimal deviation from FreeBSD GENERIC. PGSD owns the input layer
# through inputfs (per AD-1 in BACKLOG.md and the inputfs ADR series
# under inputfs/docs/adr/). To give inputfs uncontested ownership of
# HID devices, the FreeBSD HID drivers that would otherwise claim
# the same hidbus children are removed from the kernel.
#
# What stays:
#   - Everything in GENERIC by default
#   - hid     (generic HID layer, parser, descriptor handling)
#   - hidbus  (HID bus driver; inputfs attaches here per ADR 0007)
#   - usbhid  (USB-to-HID transport; required by hidbus over USB)
#
# What is removed:
#   - hms, hkbd, hgame, hcons, hsctrl, utouch, hpen, hmt, hconf
#     (HID class drivers superseded by inputfs)
#   - hidmap (HID-to-evdev mapping framework; PGSD/UTF excludes
#     evdev as a structural commitment)
#
# Rationale for hidmap removal: ADR 0007 states inputfs does not
# use hidmap. Removing it from the kernel makes the architectural
# boundary explicit. PGSD does not ship evdev as an input path.
#
# Verification target: this kernel boots, attaches inputfs to USB
# HID devices without driver competition, and passes the B.5
# bare-metal verification protocol in inputfs/docs/B5_VERIFICATION.md.

include		GENERIC

ident		PGSD

nodevice	hms
nodevice	hkbd
nodevice	hgame
nodevice	hcons
nodevice	hsctrl
nodevice	utouch
nodevice	hpen
nodevice	hmt
nodevice	hconf
nodevice	hidmap
